embeds.title: Rules
embeds.description:
Failure to follow any of these rules gives Staff the right to Mute, or kick you; in extreme cases, even a ban.

If someone is violating the rules, and staff fail to resolve the issue: Please report it to one of the Administrators (<@&1091909342736957460>)

embeds.title: Server Guidelines | Text Rules
embeds.description:
#1
Follow Discord Tos: [Terms](https://discordapp.com/terms) | [Guidelines](https://discordapp.com/guidelines)

#2
Be respectful: Treat everyone with respect, even if you disagree with them. Do not use hate speech or discriminatory language.

#3
No spamming: Do not spam the chat with repeated messages or links. If you want to share a link, make sure it's relevant to the conversation.

#4
No NSFW content: Do not share any sexually explicit or inappropriate content in the server.

#5
No trolling: Do not intentionally provoke or harass other members of the server.

#6
Keep conversations on the topic: Stay on topic in the channel you're in. If you want to talk about something else, start a new conversation in a different channel.

#7
No self-promotion: Do not promote your own content or server without permission from the server owner.

#8
No sharing personal information: Do not share personal information about yourself or others in the server.

#9
Use appropriate language: Do not use excessive swearing or vulgar language in the server.

#10
Use English: Use English as the primary language in the server. This ensures that everyone can participate in the conversation. (<#1091931702898729062> for French, Japanese, and Chinese as we have Staff Members who speak the language.)

#11
Respect privacy: Do not share personal information or conversations without permission.

#12
Do not discuss illegal activities: Do not discuss or promote illegal activities in the server.

embeds.title: Server Guidelines | Voice Rules
embeds.description:
#1
No voice chat channel hopping.

#2
No annoying, loud, or high pitch noises.

#3
Reduce the amount of background noise, if possible.

#4
Moderators reserve the right to disconnect you from a voice channel if your sound quality is poor.

#5
Moderators reserve the right to disconnect, mute, deafen, or move members to and from voice channels.

#6
Do not use voice changers: Do not use voice changers to disguise your voice or impersonate someone else.

#7
Respect privacy: Do not record or share voice conversations without permission.
